1
00:02:39,240 --> 00:02:40,680
Want to know who killed your father?

2
00:02:40,760 --> 00:02:43,360
Don't go. Uncle Punlop will kill you.

3
00:02:44,680 --> 00:02:46,440
I was just thinking about you,
my dear niece.

4
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:48,200
Rin!

5
00:02:48,920 --> 00:02:50,040
Help me.

6
00:02:50,120 --> 00:02:51,080
Who did this to you?!

7
00:02:53,000 --> 00:02:54,520
<i>Who's your boss, Uncle?</i>

8
00:02:54,600 --> 00:02:56,080
Why ask about Damon out of the blue?

9
00:02:56,960 --> 00:02:57,760
‪-Dad!
‪-Hey!

10
00:02:57,840 --> 00:03:00,200
Pok, help me! Please help my son.

11
00:03:00,280 --> 00:03:01,760
Where are my brothers?

12
00:03:02,400 --> 00:03:04,800
Where the hell are my brothers?!

13
00:03:09,800 --> 00:03:11,160
What are you doing in here?

14
00:03:13,800 --> 00:03:15,200
Answer me!

15
00:03:34,320 --> 00:03:36,640
- Quick, we need to split up.
- Let's go.

16
00:03:56,200 --> 00:03:57,960
- Found anything?
- Not yet.

17
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:09,120
Your sister's really good
at her job, my dear Te.

18
00:04:09,760 --> 00:04:11,520
She's so many times better than you.

19
00:04:11,600 --> 00:04:13,320
Everybody's praising her.

20
00:04:16,480 --> 00:04:18,600
You can take a long rest.

21
00:04:18,680 --> 00:04:21,560
Or if you want to be with your dad,

22
00:04:21,640 --> 00:04:23,760
I can send you there too.

23
00:05:12,480 --> 00:05:13,600
Hey!

24
00:05:15,640 --> 00:05:16,800
I'll check it out first.

25
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:19,160
Okay. I'll keep a lookout.

26
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:38,520
Dhammatat, is it this one?

27
00:05:38,600 --> 00:05:39,960
It needs a password.

28
00:05:41,440 --> 00:05:42,480
Just bring it back.

29
00:05:43,440 --> 00:05:44,280
<i>Okay.</i>

30
00:05:44,360 --> 00:05:46,760
- Aru, quick!
- I got it.

31
00:06:03,480 --> 00:06:04,400
What is it,

32
00:06:04,920 --> 00:06:06,320
Mr. Former CEO of 3C?

33
00:06:06,400 --> 00:06:08,200
Free Rin and bring her to me.

34
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:11,120
To you?

35
00:06:12,120 --> 00:06:13,080
Why?

36
00:06:13,680 --> 00:06:15,720
You're a vegetable.

37
00:06:16,600 --> 00:06:18,120
You don't need that many bodyguards.

38
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:20,200
She's one of my people.

39
00:06:20,280 --> 00:06:22,240
One of your people?

40
00:06:23,680 --> 00:06:26,160
Yet you let her be
with an enemy like Taiga?

41
00:06:27,560 --> 00:06:29,720
<i>Do you know how damaging that is?</i>

42
00:06:30,920 --> 00:06:33,000
You've run out of chances, Naruban.

43
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:34,960
<i>She isn't one of your people.</i>

44
00:06:35,720 --> 00:06:36,840
If you want her,

45
00:06:37,880 --> 00:06:39,000
there's only one way.

46
00:06:40,600 --> 00:06:42,160
Trade Taiga with her.

47
00:06:53,360 --> 00:06:54,440
You can open it, right?

48
00:06:58,640 --> 00:06:59,480
We must be careful.

49
00:07:00,840 --> 00:07:02,120
All the files are encrypted.

50
00:07:02,720 --> 00:07:05,040
Wherever we open it, they can trace it.

51
00:07:07,000 --> 00:07:08,440
So what do we do?

52
00:07:08,520 --> 00:07:10,240
We already got it,
yet it's so hard to open.

53
00:07:10,320 --> 00:07:11,360
Let me think.

54
00:07:13,040 --> 00:07:14,600
It must have a list of names

55
00:07:15,200 --> 00:07:16,800
and all the files about Fire Phoenix.

56
00:07:17,400 --> 00:07:19,040
We'll use it as leverage in exchange

57
00:07:19,120 --> 00:07:20,360
for the antidotes and vaccines

58
00:07:20,960 --> 00:07:22,480
and as evidence to take them down.

59
00:07:40,320 --> 00:07:41,320
What?

60
00:07:41,920 --> 00:07:45,040
What the heck? You're supposed to be
the best hacker in the universe!

61
00:07:48,040 --> 00:07:49,240
We can't be rash.

62
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:53,000
Give it to me. I'll find a way to open it.

63
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:57,560
One day.

64
00:07:58,200 --> 00:07:59,680
Give me just one day.

65
00:07:59,760 --> 00:08:01,120
I promise I can open it tomorrow.

66
00:08:20,760 --> 00:08:21,600
Ms. Nun.

67
00:08:23,560 --> 00:08:24,880
Mr. Taiga.

68
00:08:38,159 --> 00:08:39,720
Someone attacked me.

69
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:42,919
Who?

70
00:08:48,240 --> 00:08:51,240
Ms. Atinuch came in for some documents
and found you lying there.

71
00:08:51,320 --> 00:08:53,800
I was passing by,
so she asked me to stay with you.

72
00:08:53,880 --> 00:08:55,480
The doctor's on his way here.

73
00:08:58,280 --> 00:08:59,640
I'm alright.

74
00:09:05,720 --> 00:09:06,760
The security cameras.

75
00:09:13,200 --> 00:09:14,640
3C-Coin got tanked?

76
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:54,560
Calm down, Ms. Nun.

77
00:10:01,240 --> 00:10:03,040
Check the security cameras.

78
00:10:03,120 --> 00:10:04,720
Find out who broke in here.

79
00:10:13,240 --> 00:10:14,400
What are you doing in here?

80
00:10:20,360 --> 00:10:21,880
There were two of them.

81
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:23,760
They broke in here and attacked me.

82
00:10:23,840 --> 00:10:25,200
You're okay.

83
00:10:36,720 --> 00:10:38,200
I'll be right by your side.

84
00:10:40,760 --> 00:10:42,280
Please don't be afraid.

85
00:11:01,200 --> 00:11:02,920
How come 3C-Coin got tanked?

86
00:11:14,440 --> 00:11:15,280
Mom?

87
00:11:16,800 --> 00:11:18,440
Why'd you do this to me?

88
00:11:18,520 --> 00:11:20,280
You said 3C-Coin would get us rich.

89
00:11:20,360 --> 00:11:22,360
How come everyone's dumping it?

90
00:11:22,440 --> 00:11:25,240
How did its price
drop to only a few dollars?!

91
00:11:27,600 --> 00:11:28,640
Mom,

92
00:11:30,720 --> 00:11:32,160
please give me the antidote.

93
00:11:34,600 --> 00:11:36,000
Are you trying to kill me?

94
00:11:37,760 --> 00:11:38,800
I'm your son!

95
00:11:40,400 --> 00:11:41,640
<i>Are you demanding my gratitude</i>

96
00:11:41,720 --> 00:11:43,800
just because you're my mom
who bore and raised me?

97
00:11:44,400 --> 00:11:46,680
But isn't that just your duty as a wife?

98
00:11:46,760 --> 00:11:49,800
A wife my dad doesn't love
and doesn't want to be with.

99
00:11:49,880 --> 00:11:52,040
He never even intended
to make you his wife.

100
00:11:52,840 --> 00:11:55,960
This woman your dad doesn't love
and doesn't want to be with,

101
00:11:56,720 --> 00:11:58,880
who he never intended to make as his wife…

102
00:12:01,840 --> 00:12:02,880
From now on,

103
00:12:03,880 --> 00:12:06,480
she's all I'll ever be,
just like you said.

104
00:12:13,080 --> 00:12:15,920
Your dad supports you
in everything you do.

105
00:12:17,560 --> 00:12:18,960
But your sister,

106
00:12:19,720 --> 00:12:21,360
it's as if she doesn't have a dad.

107
00:12:22,400 --> 00:12:24,080
She's had to struggle to prove herself.

108
00:12:27,080 --> 00:12:28,520
Because Nun's not his daughter?

109
00:12:29,880 --> 00:12:31,080
Yes!

110
00:12:31,160 --> 00:12:32,320
But so what?

111
00:12:32,400 --> 00:12:34,080
Does that give you the right

112
00:12:34,160 --> 00:12:35,880
to insult her

113
00:12:35,960 --> 00:12:38,080
and bully her anyway you want?

114
00:12:38,960 --> 00:12:39,960
Mom…

115
00:12:44,640 --> 00:12:47,760
Think of it as giving
your sister a chance.

116
00:12:50,440 --> 00:12:53,760
Let her take 3C to another level.

117
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:56,760
And as for you,

118
00:12:57,480 --> 00:12:59,560
you can just lie down and wait here

119
00:13:00,320 --> 00:13:02,840
until I give you the antidote.

120
00:13:06,000 --> 00:13:07,840
Don't worry,

121
00:13:08,640 --> 00:13:11,000
I won't let you and your dad die.

122
00:13:11,080 --> 00:13:14,760
Everyone will be jealous
of our oh-so-perfect family.

123
00:13:16,600 --> 00:13:19,280
Just let me and your sister
become the leaders.

124
00:13:22,320 --> 00:13:24,000
Trust me, honey.

125
00:14:19,680 --> 00:14:20,920
The footage is gone,

126
00:14:21,800 --> 00:14:23,000
right when they broke in.

127
00:14:25,080 --> 00:14:26,160
That means

128
00:14:27,320 --> 00:14:29,240
they can hack our system.

129
00:14:35,520 --> 00:14:37,280
I'll have the whole system replaced.

130
00:14:41,440 --> 00:14:42,800
Good idea, Ms. Nun.

131
00:14:42,880 --> 00:14:45,240
I'm going to make 3C even more successful.

132
00:14:56,640 --> 00:14:57,880
Mr. Taiga,

133
00:14:57,960 --> 00:14:59,640
please root for me.

134
00:15:11,600 --> 00:15:13,640
We still can't open up the files.

135
00:15:13,720 --> 00:15:16,120
Dhammatat said
it should be done by tomorrow.

136
00:15:16,720 --> 00:15:18,160
How's everything on your end, Sun?

137
00:15:18,840 --> 00:15:21,720
My team's working on a code
to compromise their system.

138
00:15:21,800 --> 00:15:24,320
We're creating fake news
to trick investors,

139
00:15:24,400 --> 00:15:26,560
and we're pumping out
traps and teams of IOs.

140
00:15:27,240 --> 00:15:28,240
We're trying every way

141
00:15:28,320 --> 00:15:31,520
to tank 3C-Coin's price as hard as we can.

142
00:15:32,120 --> 00:15:33,600
It'll work, right?

143
00:15:33,680 --> 00:15:34,880
Of course.

144
00:15:34,960 --> 00:15:36,560
Good crypto traders can tell

145
00:15:36,640 --> 00:15:39,080
that losses are normal,

146
00:15:39,160 --> 00:15:42,440
but if they occur frequently,
then something's off.

147
00:15:42,520 --> 00:15:44,040
Soon,

148
00:15:44,120 --> 00:15:46,920
a 3C-coin will be worth only a rock.

149
00:15:47,680 --> 00:15:48,880
Trust me, Aru,

150
00:15:48,960 --> 00:15:51,480
when something seems too good to be true,

151
00:15:51,560 --> 00:15:52,800
you have to be careful.

152
00:15:55,160 --> 00:15:57,320
You stay safe too, Sun.

153
00:15:57,400 --> 00:15:58,520
I'm worried about you.

154
00:16:38,800 --> 00:16:40,960
Share me some of your pain

155
00:16:41,800 --> 00:16:43,280
so you can smile.

156
00:16:46,800 --> 00:16:48,200
I want to find Rin.

157
00:17:01,560 --> 00:17:03,280
Do you love her?

158
00:17:07,359 --> 00:17:08,680
I'm worried about her.

159
00:17:10,560 --> 00:17:11,960
She's sick.

160
00:17:15,440 --> 00:17:17,079
Whoever you're worried about,

161
00:17:18,240 --> 00:17:19,839
I'll worry about them too.

162
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:22,800
But if you ask me how I feel,

163
00:17:24,359 --> 00:17:26,720
I'll have to be honest…

164
00:17:28,760 --> 00:17:30,080
Love

165
00:17:31,120 --> 00:17:33,600
isn't something you can share.

166
00:17:36,240 --> 00:17:39,800
I'm not so generous that I'd feel nothing.

167
00:17:43,520 --> 00:17:45,080
It's just that I'm accepting it

168
00:17:45,800 --> 00:17:47,360
and waiting patiently

169
00:17:48,320 --> 00:17:50,760
for the day you'll be mine

170
00:17:52,520 --> 00:17:53,920
and mine alone forever.

171
00:18:17,640 --> 00:18:19,520
Can you open it yet, Dhammatat?

172
00:18:26,000 --> 00:18:27,280
Dhammatat?

173
00:18:35,440 --> 00:18:36,720
Dhammatat!

174
00:18:38,480 --> 00:18:39,600
Dhammatat!

175
00:18:44,320 --> 00:18:45,480
Dhammatat!

176
00:18:49,680 --> 00:18:51,360
Mr. Khanin!

177
00:18:54,440 --> 00:18:56,160
Mr. Khanin?

178
00:18:56,240 --> 00:18:57,640
Mr. Khanin!

179
00:18:57,720 --> 00:18:58,760
Wake up, Mr. Khanin!

180
00:18:59,560 --> 00:19:00,800
Please wake up.

181
00:19:04,040 --> 00:19:05,000
Damn you, Dhammatat!

182
00:19:06,840 --> 00:19:08,280
Where'd he go?

183
00:19:08,360 --> 00:19:10,200
He's not in this house either.

184
00:19:12,040 --> 00:19:13,000
He ran away.

185
00:19:13,800 --> 00:19:14,960
Ran away?

186
00:19:16,560 --> 00:19:17,920
To where?

187
00:19:19,240 --> 00:19:21,960
Still, that doesn't matter
as much as Mr. Naruban's flash drive.

188
00:19:23,640 --> 00:19:25,040
He has it.

189
00:19:34,440 --> 00:19:36,440
You shouldn't leave the house

190
00:19:37,680 --> 00:19:39,280
until you can open the flash drive

191
00:19:41,080 --> 00:19:43,760
and take out all the files
from Fire Phoenix.

192
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:49,800
I'll open it somewhere else,

193
00:19:50,400 --> 00:19:53,320
- so they can't trace this place.
- It's fine if they do.

194
00:19:54,080 --> 00:19:55,800
But the flash drive needs to be here,

195
00:19:56,680 --> 00:19:59,000
and all the files must be opened first.

196
00:20:06,520 --> 00:20:08,040
Who do you work for?

197
00:20:09,080 --> 00:20:10,840
You're not just some hacker, are you?

198
00:20:13,640 --> 00:20:16,080
And I take it you're not just
a police officer who got framed

199
00:20:16,880 --> 00:20:18,640
and used to work for Fire Phoenix.

200
00:20:19,720 --> 00:20:21,920
That's a really deep background check.

201
00:20:23,600 --> 00:20:26,040
You must have
a lot of skill and connections.

202
00:21:47,280 --> 00:21:48,640
The flash drive isn't here.

203
00:21:49,560 --> 00:21:51,920
So Dhammatat fooled us?

204
00:21:53,440 --> 00:21:54,760
I'm going to see Taiga.

205
00:21:55,440 --> 00:21:56,600
He and Rin aren't safe now.

206
00:21:57,200 --> 00:21:58,040
I'll come too.

207
00:21:58,120 --> 00:22:00,320
You won't be able to help me
even if you go.

208
00:22:00,400 --> 00:22:02,080
But we're a team!

209
00:22:02,160 --> 00:22:03,280
You should just stay here.

210
00:22:03,360 --> 00:22:04,440
Find out about Dhammatat.

211
00:22:04,520 --> 00:22:06,760
Tell Sun to help find him
as soon as possible.

212
00:22:10,920 --> 00:22:12,120
Ms. Ratee!

213
00:22:29,560 --> 00:22:32,480
PERMANENTLY CLOSED!!!

214
00:22:41,880 --> 00:22:44,960
PERMANENTLY CLOSED!!!

215
00:22:45,560 --> 00:22:47,400
I can't find Dhammatat at all.

216
00:22:48,160 --> 00:22:51,040
Mr. Naruban's flash drive is gone too.

217
00:22:57,280 --> 00:23:01,040
Who knows what information
he's got already.

218
00:23:01,120 --> 00:23:02,800
Relax, Aru.

219
00:23:03,480 --> 00:23:04,840
I'll help you find it.

220
00:23:08,240 --> 00:23:10,120
I'm sorry, Sun.

221
00:23:10,200 --> 00:23:13,000
You're already busy enough
with the 3C-Coin thing,

222
00:23:13,080 --> 00:23:15,120
since you got its price so low.

223
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:16,440
No worries.

224
00:23:16,960 --> 00:23:19,240
Turning fake news into real news

225
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:21,280
isn't hard to do.

226
00:23:22,160 --> 00:23:24,760
With investments, knowledge does matter,

227
00:23:24,840 --> 00:23:26,560
but keeping a level head matters the most.

228
00:23:26,640 --> 00:23:30,600
People who aren't level-headed
tend to believe it when they hear,

229
00:23:30,680 --> 00:23:32,560
"An insider told me this."

230
00:23:33,560 --> 00:23:35,680
Then, they're trapped by their own greed,

231
00:23:35,760 --> 00:23:37,520
and the fake news

232
00:23:37,600 --> 00:23:39,680
will drive the coin's price down

233
00:23:39,760 --> 00:23:41,280
even further.

234
00:23:42,360 --> 00:23:44,520
We need to make 3C pay, no matter what.

235
00:23:45,480 --> 00:23:47,240
We need to find Rin.

236
00:24:08,800 --> 00:24:12,240
I never expected
that Dhammatat would betray us!

237
00:24:12,320 --> 00:24:15,280
Till now, we still can't find him.

238
00:24:18,480 --> 00:24:19,720
Taiga,

239
00:24:20,280 --> 00:24:22,760
Dhammatat knows everything
about you and Rin.

240
00:24:23,880 --> 00:24:25,120
You have to be careful

241
00:24:25,200 --> 00:24:28,360
because now, everyone around you
is a member of Fire Phoenix.

242
00:24:39,800 --> 00:24:41,160
And so are you, right?

243
00:25:04,680 --> 00:25:05,880
Yes.

244
00:25:07,440 --> 00:25:09,600
I used to be in Fire Phoenix.

245
00:25:12,320 --> 00:25:13,840
I used to throw people

246
00:25:13,920 --> 00:25:16,440
who stood in their way in jail.

247
00:25:17,640 --> 00:25:18,840
Until one day,

248
00:25:18,920 --> 00:25:22,320
I was betrayed by my boss,
whom I trusted and believed in the most.

249
00:25:25,480 --> 00:25:28,160
I was the scapegoat
for a crime I didn't commit.

250
00:25:30,920 --> 00:25:34,480
So I asked myself,
"What did I do all that for?"

251
00:25:38,400 --> 00:25:40,080
As an honorable policeman,

252
00:25:41,600 --> 00:25:44,520
I shouldn't have to serve those outlaws.

253
00:25:45,720 --> 00:25:47,560
So I decided to walk away.

254
00:25:50,440 --> 00:25:51,640
But then…

255
00:25:55,840 --> 00:25:57,960
my family got murdered.

256
00:26:01,960 --> 00:26:03,160
Just like your family did.

257
00:26:13,040 --> 00:26:15,680
I'll never forgive Fire Phoenix.

258
00:26:17,720 --> 00:26:19,560
I'll go after Damon

259
00:26:19,640 --> 00:26:21,320
for ordering everyone's murder.

260
00:26:46,040 --> 00:26:47,640
What took you so long,

261
00:26:48,440 --> 00:26:49,840
Lieutenant Dhammatat?

262
00:26:56,520 --> 00:26:58,000
What did you get?

263
00:27:01,960 --> 00:27:03,360
It was in Naruban's office, Boss.

264
00:27:05,840 --> 00:27:06,920
What's in it?

265
00:27:07,880 --> 00:27:09,040
I still can't open it.

266
00:27:09,920 --> 00:27:10,920
It’s heavily encrypted.

267
00:27:11,000 --> 00:27:12,640
Even a pro like you can't do it?

268
00:27:14,160 --> 00:27:15,480
I'm sorry.

269
00:27:16,000 --> 00:27:17,000
I tried.

270
00:27:17,800 --> 00:27:18,640
‪But…

271
00:27:19,200 --> 00:27:20,920
If you give me more time, I will--

272
00:27:23,200 --> 00:27:24,920
Take out all the files.

273
00:27:28,920 --> 00:27:29,760
Okay, Boss.

274
00:27:35,280 --> 00:27:36,120
Boss?

275
00:27:38,240 --> 00:27:40,280
Once I can access the files…

276
00:27:43,320 --> 00:27:45,360
can I stop going undercover?

277
00:27:46,680 --> 00:27:48,440
You work in secret,

278
00:27:49,280 --> 00:27:50,560
yet you want to back out?

279
00:27:51,880 --> 00:27:53,720
You really think your victims

280
00:27:54,560 --> 00:27:56,120
will let you off easy?

281
00:27:56,960 --> 00:27:58,960
I want to live a normal life, Boss.

282
00:28:00,920 --> 00:28:02,040
I want to quit.

283
00:28:06,440 --> 00:28:08,080
You're very skilled.

284
00:28:09,960 --> 00:28:12,200
I chose you for such an important job

285
00:28:13,160 --> 00:28:14,760
because you don't seem like a cop.

286
00:28:17,800 --> 00:28:20,880
You went undercover for years
until Taiga trusted you.

287
00:28:22,080 --> 00:28:23,640
That must've been so hard.

288
00:28:24,640 --> 00:28:25,760
So?

289
00:28:25,840 --> 00:28:28,160
Do you see those people
as your true friends now?

290
00:28:32,080 --> 00:28:33,720
I don't want to fool anyone anymore, Boss.

291
00:28:35,560 --> 00:28:37,240
Friendship is good.

292
00:28:38,240 --> 00:28:41,360
But the world's justice matters more.

293
00:28:42,920 --> 00:28:44,920
We can't choose how we die,

294
00:28:45,000 --> 00:28:46,520
but we can choose how we live.

295
00:28:47,600 --> 00:28:49,360
How do you want people to remember you?

296
00:28:52,560 --> 00:28:54,840
An ordinary man, Boss.

297
00:29:01,640 --> 00:29:02,560
Okay.

298
00:29:05,080 --> 00:29:06,560
Maybe you're feeling pressured today.

299
00:29:07,400 --> 00:29:08,800
But let me warn you.

300
00:29:08,880 --> 00:29:10,920
Whenever you reveal your identity,

301
00:29:11,520 --> 00:29:13,360
those who you believe are your friends

302
00:29:13,440 --> 00:29:16,000
will be ready to trample on you
and despise you.

303
00:29:16,080 --> 00:29:17,360
They'll never welcome you again.

304
00:29:17,960 --> 00:29:19,240
Until then,

305
00:29:19,320 --> 00:29:20,720
what you should do

306
00:29:20,800 --> 00:29:22,880
is uphold what's right.

307
00:29:23,720 --> 00:29:26,080
Fire Phoenix will make the world better.

308
00:29:26,160 --> 00:29:27,840
And for every change,

309
00:29:27,920 --> 00:29:30,120
those who sacrificed
will be remembered and praised.

310
00:29:33,080 --> 00:29:35,120
If you want the world

311
00:29:35,200 --> 00:29:36,720
to stay the same,

312
00:29:37,320 --> 00:29:39,000
then go back to them.

313
00:29:39,080 --> 00:29:40,280
Go back to that life

314
00:29:40,960 --> 00:29:42,760
where all you can be…

315
00:29:45,080 --> 00:29:46,560
is some silly hacker.

316
00:30:23,680 --> 00:30:25,520
I can still trust you, right?

317
00:30:35,720 --> 00:30:38,240
Hey, how'd you follow me here?

318
00:30:39,520 --> 00:30:40,600
In your backpack.

319
00:30:46,960 --> 00:30:49,520
A tracker? When did you put it in here?

320
00:30:49,600 --> 00:30:51,480
I put it there to track Taiga.

321
00:30:52,360 --> 00:30:54,360
I didn't think it'd be helpful one day

322
00:30:55,080 --> 00:30:56,440
for finding a backstabbing friend.

323
00:31:10,040 --> 00:31:12,400
Fire Phoenix' files aren't in here.

324
00:31:12,920 --> 00:31:14,440
I used a replica to fool my boss.

325
00:31:17,840 --> 00:31:19,400
Come on. Let's go somewhere else first.

326
00:31:27,720 --> 00:31:29,480
You can open it, right?

327
00:31:33,400 --> 00:31:36,240
We must be careful.
All the files are encrypted.

328
00:31:36,320 --> 00:31:39,000
Wherever we open it, they can trace it.

329
00:31:57,800 --> 00:31:59,880
The flash drive in your office

330
00:32:01,400 --> 00:32:02,840
has been stolen.

331
00:32:05,320 --> 00:32:06,360
The flash drive

332
00:32:06,440 --> 00:32:09,560
holds the password that can be used
to access every member's info.

333
00:32:12,480 --> 00:32:14,320
But what matters more than the info

334
00:32:15,720 --> 00:32:16,760
is the mask.

335
00:32:19,240 --> 00:32:20,760
Fire Phoenix' mask.

336
00:32:25,480 --> 00:32:26,880
You need it for meetings.

337
00:32:27,960 --> 00:32:29,560
No one reveals their identity.

338
00:32:32,880 --> 00:32:34,880
Find a way to get into my home

339
00:32:34,960 --> 00:32:36,560
and take it.

340
00:32:38,040 --> 00:32:41,560
There's only one week left
before Fire Phoenix has a big meeting.

341
00:33:38,160 --> 00:33:40,600
BABY, CATCH ME IF YOU CAN

342
00:33:48,280 --> 00:33:50,600
Hey, stop right there!

343
00:34:11,159 --> 00:34:14,440
I'm sure Punlop
will attend Fire Phoenix' meeting.

344
00:34:14,520 --> 00:34:16,239
You have to be careful, Taiga,

345
00:34:17,040 --> 00:34:18,800
because if he recognizes you,

346
00:34:18,880 --> 00:34:21,199
you'll be in danger,
even if you're behind the mask.

347
00:34:23,880 --> 00:34:25,840
I don't think it's just the mask

348
00:34:27,040 --> 00:34:28,480
that allows us to go in there.

349
00:34:32,480 --> 00:34:35,960
If Dhammatat were still with us,
everything would be easier.

350
00:34:43,560 --> 00:34:45,639
Dhammatat's a part of Fire Phoenix too.

351
00:34:46,880 --> 00:34:47,920
I don't think so.

352
00:34:49,639 --> 00:34:52,280
I had my friends who are ex-cops
look into him.

353
00:34:52,880 --> 00:34:54,760
He's not a part of them.

354
00:34:54,840 --> 00:34:56,360
He's just one of Punlop's henchmen.

355
00:34:57,280 --> 00:34:58,960
I overlooked it.

356
00:34:59,040 --> 00:35:02,880
I never doubted
why Dhammatat knew far too much,

357
00:35:02,960 --> 00:35:05,160
far too much for an ordinary hacker.

358
00:35:13,840 --> 00:35:15,200
Just because of friendship,

359
00:35:17,360 --> 00:35:18,800
we let our guard down.

360
00:35:27,800 --> 00:35:29,040
Taiga,

361
00:35:29,880 --> 00:35:31,200
if this time,

362
00:35:32,240 --> 00:35:35,640
you're going to the core of Fire Phoenix
to destroy it from the inside,

363
00:35:37,000 --> 00:35:38,320
we need to take the passcode,

364
00:35:38,920 --> 00:35:40,200
the meeting location,

365
00:35:41,160 --> 00:35:43,400
and the updated information from Naruban.

366
00:36:19,760 --> 00:36:20,680
Punlop.

367
00:36:46,800 --> 00:36:49,400
A reward for a man who's no longer needed.

368
00:36:53,160 --> 00:36:54,240
Rest in peace.

369
00:36:56,240 --> 00:36:57,840
Die a slow death.

370
00:37:01,000 --> 00:37:02,320
Or if you can't take it…

371
00:37:05,040 --> 00:37:06,680
just let your heart stop beating.

372
00:37:12,440 --> 00:37:13,800
A lousy husband like you

373
00:37:15,000 --> 00:37:17,280
shouldn't get to live
and torture Mrs. Giranun.

374
00:37:35,680 --> 00:37:38,200
Let's welcome our new shareholder.

375
00:37:38,280 --> 00:37:40,520
He's a famous media mogul in the US

376
00:37:40,600 --> 00:37:44,080
who's eager to invest with 3C Group
to build a new future

377
00:37:44,160 --> 00:37:45,640
for Thailand.

378
00:37:48,440 --> 00:37:51,240
Mr. Robert told us
that he's sent his representative

379
00:37:51,320 --> 00:37:52,400
named

380
00:37:52,920 --> 00:37:56,840
Ms. Rateerungsri Clay.

381
00:38:09,440 --> 00:38:11,000
Good afternoon, everyone.

382
00:38:21,680 --> 00:38:23,680
<i>What can 3C-Coin even do</i>

383
00:38:24,280 --> 00:38:25,960
other than tank more and more every day?

384
00:38:28,600 --> 00:38:30,960
When it profited us,
you never got involved.

385
00:38:32,000 --> 00:38:33,080
Okay.

386
00:38:34,480 --> 00:38:36,000
From now on, we need to work together.

387
00:38:36,880 --> 00:38:39,440
I have the right to speak, give orders,

388
00:38:40,720 --> 00:38:42,360
and veto everything.

389
00:38:47,600 --> 00:38:49,280
- If you're here to pick a fight--
- Stop it, Ms. Nun.

390
00:38:50,640 --> 00:38:52,800
Remember why I'm here.

391
00:38:54,080 --> 00:38:55,160
I'm a shareholder.

392
00:38:56,080 --> 00:38:58,720
Please use your brain
more than your emotions.

393
00:39:01,200 --> 00:39:03,480
I'll forget everything that's happened

394
00:39:03,560 --> 00:39:04,880
to let you redeem yourself.

395
00:39:18,480 --> 00:39:20,360
Let's work together,

396
00:39:21,640 --> 00:39:25,160
so that 3C-Coin's value
will profit us both.

397
00:39:25,760 --> 00:39:27,360
Does that sound good, Ms. Ratee?

398
00:39:39,240 --> 00:39:41,440
The router's dead.

399
00:39:41,520 --> 00:39:44,440
We'll give you a replacement.
I happened to bring one.

400
00:39:44,520 --> 00:39:46,200
- I'll go grab it.
- Huh?

401
00:39:47,320 --> 00:39:49,120
What's up?

402
00:39:49,720 --> 00:39:50,960
No, thanks!

403
00:39:51,520 --> 00:39:53,440
I'm not buying a lotto this time.

404
00:39:53,520 --> 00:39:56,800
I don't care if there's a lucky number
or a guru!

405
00:40:28,120 --> 00:40:29,400
Wait.

406
00:40:54,520 --> 00:40:56,040
You're looking for this, right?

407
00:41:05,760 --> 00:41:07,200
How's my dad doing?

408
00:41:08,560 --> 00:41:09,720
Not very well.

409
00:41:10,800 --> 00:41:12,240
He's still alive, right?

410
00:41:13,000 --> 00:41:14,200
Yes.

411
00:41:14,920 --> 00:41:18,240
My dad once told me
he's keeping something very important.

412
00:41:20,640 --> 00:41:22,560
I did some searching and found this.

413
00:41:26,840 --> 00:41:29,520
It's not something unimportant
that anyone can have.

414
00:41:33,600 --> 00:41:36,400
Hurry up and go.
I disabled the alarm, but it won't be long

415
00:41:36,480 --> 00:41:37,640
before it goes off.

416
00:41:50,840 --> 00:41:52,000
Are you okay?

417
00:41:52,880 --> 00:41:53,760
Go, now!

418
00:41:55,440 --> 00:41:56,480
Go!

419
00:42:47,320 --> 00:42:48,960
We should thank your husband

420
00:42:49,960 --> 00:42:51,520
for always working so hard.

421
00:42:54,800 --> 00:42:57,400
The virus from 3C
is about to conquer the world.

422
00:42:59,160 --> 00:43:00,240
The virus,

423
00:43:00,800 --> 00:43:02,040
the vaccine,

424
00:43:02,760 --> 00:43:03,880
and the cure

425
00:43:04,400 --> 00:43:06,080
can only be bought with 3C-coins.

426
00:43:09,400 --> 00:43:11,760
He and his son never told me much at all.

427
00:43:13,240 --> 00:43:15,120
My life's like a flower,

428
00:43:15,880 --> 00:43:17,160
beautiful,

429
00:43:17,240 --> 00:43:19,120
but worth nothing to them.

430
00:43:26,800 --> 00:43:28,560
Thank you so much, Punlop.

431
00:43:30,360 --> 00:43:34,120
You're the only one who sees my worth.

432
00:43:44,600 --> 00:43:46,680
I know you're not just a fragrant flower.

433
00:43:47,760 --> 00:43:49,200
You're beautiful,

434
00:43:49,960 --> 00:43:51,120
precious,

435
00:43:52,960 --> 00:43:54,280
and smart.

436
00:43:56,720 --> 00:43:58,480
You make people fall in love with you

437
00:43:59,840 --> 00:44:01,360
so much, they'd give you their lives.

438
00:44:52,000 --> 00:44:53,120
Taiga.

439
00:44:55,080 --> 00:44:57,280
Naruban's in a coma.
He can't attend the meeting.

440
00:44:57,360 --> 00:44:58,280
The passcode will be erased.

441
00:44:59,240 --> 00:45:00,760
If you use his mask to attend it,

442
00:45:00,840 --> 00:45:02,120
you'll get caught for sure.

443
00:45:13,040 --> 00:45:14,600
<i>Mr. Punlop will be working with us.</i>

444
00:45:14,680 --> 00:45:17,720
- To do what?
- Executive secretary to the CEO.

445
00:45:18,480 --> 00:45:20,920
Wait, how come
you didn't get the email like we did?

446
00:45:29,840 --> 00:45:33,360
<i>I don't have a lot of time left.</i>
<i>The side effects of the antidote</i>

447
00:45:33,440 --> 00:45:35,000
<i>has changed my body.</i>

448
00:45:35,080 --> 00:45:36,120
The symptoms are similar to…

449
00:45:36,200 --> 00:45:37,320
Cancer?!

450
00:46:06,200 --> 00:46:08,200
Subtitle translation by:
Ramil Natnitiwitaya
